# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules
# Enforce HTTPS, non-www, and trailing slashes to prevent duplicate content

# Force HTTPS and non-www (handled by Cloudflare dashboard settings)
# Note: Configure in Cloudflare dashboard:
# - SSL/TLS → Edge Certificates → Always Use HTTPS: ON
# - DNS → CNAME for www pointing to maantis.com with Proxied enabled
# - Page Rules → www.maantis.com/* → Forwarding URL (301) → https://maantis.com/$1

# Redirect URLs without trailing slash to version with trailing slash (301 permanent)
/about  /about/  301!
/services  /services/  301!
/blog  /blog/  301!
/services/website-development  /services/website-development/  301!
/services/cloud-infrastructure  /services/cloud-infrastructure/  301!
/services/performance-engineering  /services/performance-engineering/  301!
/services/distributed-systems  /services/distributed-systems/  301!

# Redirect blog posts without trailing slash
/blog/the-mantis-shrimp-principle  /blog/the-mantis-shrimp-principle/  301!
/blog/welcome-to-maantis  /blog/welcome-to-maantis/  301!
/blog/wordpress-is-costing-you-twice-as-much  /blog/wordpress-is-costing-you-twice-as-much/  301!

# 404 fallback
/*  /404.html  404
